"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-08-05-paris-2024-olympics-oborodudu-loses-semi-final-bout\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Blessing Oborodudu failed to clinch a place in the final of the women's 68kg wrestling, losing to Kyrgyzstan's Meerim Zhumanazarova, who won the semi-final bout 3-1 on points.  Oborodudu sustained an injury, which affected her performance in the bout. She will now battle for bronze medal on Tuesday.  The 35-year-old won her two previous bouts on Monday against Canadian and French opponents.  She won silver in the same event three years ago in Tokyo.  UEFA Champions League play-off draw confirmed [Full list]  Transfer: Man Utd drop interest in Ugarte  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's dismal performance worries enthusiasts  Paris 2024 Olympics: D'Tigress' Wakama wins Best Coach award  Paris 2024 Olympics: Brume vows to  bounce back from disappointing outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Sports Minister apologises to Nigerians after disastrous outing  Paris 2024 Olympics: Team Nigeria officially finishes without single medal  Paris 2024 Olympics: Nigeria's last medal hope Reuben crashes out in Wrestling  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"